WPP Project - Open Source Licenses
===================================

This project integrates code from multiple open source projects.
Below is the complete license information for all components.

## WPP Core Code

Copyright (C) 2026 WPP Project Contributors

This program is free software: you can redistribute it and/or modify
it under the terms of the GNU General Public License as published by
the Free Software Foundation, either version 3 of the License, or
(at your option) any later version.

See LICENSE file for the complete GPL 3.0 text.

## Third-Party Components

### SQLite Database Engine
- **License**: Public Domain
- **Source**: third_party/sqlite/
- **License File**: LICENSES/SQLITE-LICENSE
- **Usage**: Modified and integrated into wpp-sqlite module
- **Restrictions**: None - completely free to use and modify

### TinyCC Compiler
- **License**: GNU Lesser General Public License v2.1 (LGPL 2.1)
- **Source**: third_party/tinycc/
- **License File**: LICENSES/TINYCC-LICENSE
- **Usage**: Wrapped in wpp-compiler module
- **Restrictions**: Modifications must be open-sourced under LGPL

### SQTP Protocol & JavaScript Libraries
- **License**: MIT License
- **Source**: docs/sqtp/ (protocol specification), lib/sqtp/ (JavaScript libraries)
- **License File**: LICENSES/SQTP-LICENSE
- **Components**:
  * SQTP/1.0 Protocol Specification
  * sqtp.xhr.promise.js - Promise-based client
  * sqtp.xhr.callback.js - Callback-based client
  * sqtp.fetch.js - Fetch API client
- **Usage**: Can be used independently in any project
- **Restrictions**: Must include MIT license text in redistributions

### althttpd Web Server
- **License**: Public Domain (expected, confirmation pending)
- **Source**: third_party/althttpd/
- **License File**: LICENSES/ALTHTTPD-LICENSE (to be added)
- **Usage**: Modified and integrated into wpp-server module
- **Restrictions**: None - completely free to use and modify

## Module License Summary

| Module | License | Can Modify | Must Share Source |
|--------|---------|------------|-------------------|
| wpp-core | GPL 3.0 | ✓ | ✓ |
| wpp-sqlite | Public Domain | ✓ | ✗ |
| wpp-compiler | LGPL 2.1 | ✓ | ✓ (if distributed) |
| wpp-server | Public Domain | ✓ | ✗ |
| sqtp-protocol | MIT | ✓ | ✗ |
| sqtp-libraries | MIT | ✓ | ✗ |

## License Compatibility

The overall project is licensed under GPL 3.0, which is compatible with:
- Public Domain code (SQLite, althttpd)
- LGPL 2.1 code (TinyCC)
- MIT License code (SQTP protocol and libraries)

All components can be legally integrated under GPL 3.0.

Note: SQTP protocol specification and JavaScript libraries are independently
licensed under MIT License, allowing their use in non-GPL projects.

